%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tesla%20recalls%20120%2C000%20cars%20over%20faulty%20doors%20that%20could%20open%20during%20a%20crash%2C%20just%20a%20week%20after%20its%20largest-ever%20recall%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224633%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20logo%20marks%20the%20showroom%20and%20service%20center%20for%20the%20US%20automotive%20and%20energy%20company%20Tesla%20in%20Amsterdam%20on%20October%2023%2C%202019%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6586a44fab6f2ebb11f69f8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223202%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETesla%20is%20facing%20it's%20fourteenth%20recall%20this%20year.%3Cp%3EJOHN%20THYS%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETesla%20is%20recalling%20more%20than%20120%2C000%20cars%20due%20to%20doors%20that%20could%20open%20during%20crashes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20issue%20could%20occur%20in%20some%20Model%20S%20and%20Model%20X%20vehicles%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELast%20week%2C%20around%202%20million%20Teslas%20were%20recalled%20in%20the%20US%20over%20the%20Autopilot%20feature.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20is%20recalling%20more%20than%20120%2C000%20vehicles%20in%20the%20US%20after%20engineers%20discovered%20that%20doors%20on%20certain%20models%20could%20open%20during%20a%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20faulty%20doors%20have%20been%20found%20in%20some%202021-2023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-model-s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EModel%20S%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-model-x-suv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EModel%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.nhtsa.gov%2Fodi%2Frcl%2F2023%2FRCLRPT-23V862-1183.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiling%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20National%20Highway%20Traffic%20Safety%20Administration%20(NHTSA)%2C%20Tesla%20said%20that%20in%20testing%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20engineers%20had%20%26quot%3Bobserved%20a%20cabin%20door%20unlatch%20after%20impact%20on%20the%20non-struck%20side.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20test%20vehicle%20was%20found%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Boperating%20without%20the%20lockout%20functionality%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20the%20company%20said%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Binadvertently%20excluded%20from%20the%20affected%20vehicles%26quot%3B%20through%20software%20updates%20it%20began%20releasing%20in%20late%20September%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20means%20that%20the%20vehicles%20fail%20to%20meet%20federal%20safety%20standards%20for%20side-impact%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20aware%20of%20any%20warranty%20claims%20or%20injuries%20relating%20to%20this%20condition%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20has%20issued%20a%20free%20over-the-air%20software%20update%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation%2C%20with%20owners%20of%20the%20affected%20vehicles%20due%20to%20be%20notified%20on%20February%2017%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NHTSA%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos-transportation%2Ftesla-recall-over-120000-vehicles-us-nhtsa-2023-12-22%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20had%20not%20evaluated%20the%20company's%20solution%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20it%20only%20received%20the%20software%20update%20on%20the%20vehicles%20it%20owns%20a%20few%20days%20ago.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20red%20Tesla%20Model%20X%20SUV%20is%20pictured%20with%20rocky%20hills%20and%20a%20blue%20sky%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F649f2dceaa56b70019ca8ea0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Model%20X%20is%20Tesla's%20large%20family%20SUV.%3Cp%3ETesla%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20just%20a%20week%20after%20the%20company%20had%20to%20recall%20almost%20all%20of%20its%20US%20vehicles%20over%20an%20issue%20with%20its%20Autopilot%20feature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%202%20million%20Tesla%20vehicles%20were%20part%20of%20the%20recall%2C%20which%20followed%20a%20two-year%20NHTSA%20investigation%20that%20found%20that%20the%20driver-assistance%20system%20did%20not%20do%20enough%20to%20prevent%20drivers%20from%20misusing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20is%20offering%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-recalls-2-million-cars-as-regulators-say-autopilot-insufficent-2023-12%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520February%252C%2520Tesla%2520issued%2520a%2Cwhat%2520you%2520want%2520to%2520know.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20software%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20some%202012-2023%20Model%20S%3B%202016-2023%20Model%20X%3Cu%3E%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%202017-2023%20Model%203%3B%20and%202020-2023%20Model%20Y%20vehicles%20equipped%20with%20Autosteer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20BI's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-recalls-model-x-s-over-faulty-doors-crashes-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703334143000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6586a474cefc010bea26f536%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-recalls-model-x-s-over-faulty-doors-crashes-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tesla%20said%20that%20in%20testing%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20engineers%20had%20%26quot%3Bobserved%20a%20cabin%20door%20unlatch%20after%20impact%20on%20the%20non-struck%20side.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40insider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-recalls-model-x-s-over-faulty-doors-crashes-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20thought%20drinking%20until%20I%20blacked%20out%20most%20nights%20was%20normal.%20College%20drinking%20culture%20masked%20my%20alcoholism.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Evan%20Lambert%20on%20Dartmouth's%20campus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571f2bc58e7c0c29a2aa589%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20at%20Dartmouth.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Evan%20Lambert%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20I%20enrolled%20at%20Dartmouth%2C%20I%20drank%20most%20nights%20of%20the%20week%20and%20attended%20frat%20parties.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20didn't%20know%20I%20had%20a%20problem%20because%20college%20party%20culture%20normalized%20over-drinking.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20my%20late%2020s%2C%20I%20got%20sober.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20attended%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fincoming-harvard-university-freshman-tuition-financial-aid-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efreshman%20orientation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Dartmouth%20in%202007%2C%20I%20met%20Keggy%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20Portly%2C%20gregarious%2C%20and%20prone%20to%20spontaneous%20dancing%2C%20he%20was%20both%20an%20outsize%20presence%20and%20a%20perfect%20distillation%20of%20our%20school%20spirit.%20His%20name%20was%20Keggy%20the%20Keg%20because%20he%20was%20a%20life-size%2C%20well%2C%20beer%20keg%2C%20and%20he%20was%20Dartmouth%20College's%20unofficial%20mascot.%20In%20addition%20to%20being%20ever-so-slightly%20on%20the%20nose%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-freshman-what-my-first-day-of-classes-was-like-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eundergraduate%20program%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20was%20also%20a%20sign%20of%20things%20to%20come%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20get%20me%20wrong%3A%20I%20had%20many%20great%20college%20experiences.%20I%20met%20some%20wonderful%20friends%20and%20professors%20and%20uncovered%20a%20treasure%20trove%20of%20courses%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-join-extracurriculars-just-to-buff-up-college-application-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eextracurricular%20activities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20where%20I%20discovered%20an%20affinity%20for%20creative%20writing%3B%20my%20school%20even%20launched%20me%20into%20a%20journalism%20grad%20program%20and%20a%20modest%20writing%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Funiversity-of-alabama-rush-experience-miserable-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efraternities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20monopolized%20our%20social%20lives.%20And%20we%20were%20horny%2C%20high-achieving%2018-year-olds%20with%20pressure%20%E2%80%94%20both%20familial%20and%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20on%20our%20shoulders.%20We%20were%20also%20raised%20on%20movies%20like%20%26quot%3BRevenge%20of%20the%20Nerds%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BOld%20School%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BVan%20Wilder%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20taught%20us%20to%20view%20college%20as%20a%20never-ending%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20all%20of%20these%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20like%20bolts%20of%20lightning%20in%20a%20plasma%20ball%20%E2%80%94%20collided%20quietly.%20The%20result%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-i-answer-the-question-why-arent-you-drinking-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emy%20drinking%20problem%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20unnoticed%20%E2%80%94%20even%20by%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmerican%20college%20culture%20sent%20me%20over%20the%20edge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20already%20struggling%20mentally%20when%20I%20received%20my%20college-admissions%20letter.%20An%20anxious%2C%20hardworking%20gay%20teen%20coming%20from%20a%20conservative%2C%20often%20homophobic%20city%20with%20a%20depressing%20lack%20of%20fellow%20queers%2C%20I%20was%20not%20just%20high-strung%2C%20but%20emotionally%20repressed%20and%20starving%20for%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20first%20few%20blackouts%20during%20my%20first%20semester%2C%20I%20became%20more%20interested%20in%20drinking%20than%20in%20investing%20in%20my%20future.%20I%20joined%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbama-rush-university-alabama-sorority-racism-segregation-discrimination-history-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eco-ed%20fraternity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20embraced%20the%20accepted%20college-age%20persona%20of%20being%20an%20avid%20drinker.%20Ever%20the%20high%20achiever%2C%20I%20even%20augmented%20my%20weekend%20drinking%20schedule%20by%20partying%20on%20weekdays%2C%20effectively%20turning%20my%20drinking%20into%20an%20extracurricular%20activity.%20One%20of%20my%20crowning%20achievements%20was%20being%20selected%20to%20represent%20my%20co-ed%20society%20at%20a%20campus-wide%20beer-pong%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20one%20offered%20help%20because%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20was%20considered%20normal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20%E2%80%94%20not%20once%20%E2%80%94%20considered%20myself%20an%20alcoholic.%20Since%20we%20were%20in%20college%2C%20%26quot%3Bblacking%20out%20a%20lot%26quot%3B%20passed%20as%20a%20personality.%20As%20long%20as%20I%20was%20following%20conventional%20binge-drinking%20practices%20(don't%20drink%20alone%2C%20don't%20respond%20to%20emails%20drunk%2C%20don't%20get%20caught%20by%20the%20police)%2C%20I%20never%20seemed%20to%20attract%20unwanted%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20time%2C%20to%20avoid%20being%20caught%20by%20the%20cops%20stumbling%20down%20Frat%20Row%2C%20I%20dropped%20to%20the%20ground%20and%20started%20making%20snow%20angels.%20My%20friends%20laughed%20and%20laughed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20only%20one%20person%20ever%20called%20me%20an%20alcoholic%20during%20my%20entire%20time%20in%20school%2C%20and%20she%20was%20only%20joking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20real%20problems%20arose%20after%20I%20graduated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20my%20drinking%20adventures%2C%20and%20subsequent%20academic%20delinquency%2C%20led%20me%20into%20deep%20sadness%2C%20I%20always%20rebounded.%20Protected%20from%20the%20real%20world%20by%20our%20college%20bubble%2C%20I%20never%20connected%20the%20dots%20and%20traced%20my%20mental%20unwellness%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ffacing-back-to-school-when-your-kid-may-not-make-it-back-to-school-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eback%20to%20alcohol%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20I%20had%20to%20enter%20the%20job%20market%20beset%20with%20mounting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstop-blaming-me-for-student-loan-debt-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudent-loan%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20direction%2C%20I%20realized%20some%20things.%20My%20drinking%20habits%20didn't%20subside%20and%20without%20the%20college-party%20context%2C%20my%20drinking%20problem%20became%20all%20too%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnhappy%20and%20unmoored%2C%20I%20spent%20my%20first%20years%20of%20adulthood%20in%20a%20state%20of%20perpetual%20disappointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quit%20drinking%20three%20times%20before%20finally%20making%20it%20stick%20in%20my%20late%2020s.%20I'm%20now%20six%20years%20sober.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20can't%20help%20thinking%20that%20I%20might%20have%20been%20better%20off%20taking%20a%20gap%20year%20before%20college.%20Then%20I%20could%20have%20gone%20to%20therapy%2C%20or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20watched%20some%20less%20positive%20movies%20about%20Greek%20life.%20If%20I'd%20seen%20the%20dismal%20slasher%20flick%20%26quot%3BSorority%20Row%26quot%3B%20before%20matriculating%2C%20then%20maybe%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20so%20eager%20to%20play%20beer%20pong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20Note%3A%20Jana%20Barnello%2C%20a%20media-relations%20strategist%20at%20Dartmouth%2C%20added%20the%20following%20comment%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BAt%20Dartmouth%2C%20the%20health%20and%20safety%20of%20our%20community%20is%20of%20paramount%20importance.%20We%20are%20committed%20to%20working%20with%20Greek%20organizations%20to%20ensure%20a%20culture%20of%20accountability%2C%20inclusivity%2C%20and%20safety.%20We%20hold%20all%20student%20organizations%20at%20Dartmouth%20to%20a%20high%20standard%20of%20conduct%20and%20accountability%20with%20the%20expectation%20that%20they%20will%20contribute%20to%20a%20respectful%20and%20inclusive%20environment%2C%20help%20to%20shape%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20future%2C%20and%20elevate%20%E2%80%94%20not%20denigrate%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Dartmouth%20experience.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BIn%202011%2C%20the%20Dartmouth%20Health%20Service%20primary-care%20clinic%20began%20universal%20screening%20for%20high-risk%20drinking%20and%20since%202015%2C%20hard%20alcohol%20has%20been%20banned%20on%20campus%2C%20which%20includes%20Greek%20spaces.%20These%20changes%2C%20among%20other%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudents.dartmouth.edu%2Fwellness-center%2Fprevention-education%2Falcohol-other-drugs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Esubstance%20use%20reduction%20initiatives%20and%20programs%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20the%20mandatory%20first-year%20student%20online%20alcohol%20education%20class%20%E2%80%94%20are%20ongoing%20commitments%20to%20prioritizing%20student%20health%20and%20well-being.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-drinking-culture-greek-life-alcoholism-blacking-out-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publi