rces%20to%20train%20new%20employees%20and%20you%20might%20be%20expected%20to%20wear%20many%20hats%20at%20a%20startup%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Big%20Tech%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-unwritten-rules-of-working-at-a-startup-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20startups%20typically%20have%20no%20time%20%3C%2Fa%3Eor%20resources%20to%20train%20their%20employees%2C%20so%20you%20must%20already%20have%20the%20exact%20skills%20they%20need%20when%20applying%20for%20a%20job.%20The%20startups%20I%20worked%20for%20had%20no%20orientation%20or%20training%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20be%20prepared%20to%20work%20extra%20hours.%20At%20a%20startup%2C%20you%20will%20wear%20many%20hats%20because%20resources%20might%20be%20limited.%20That%20means%20you%20might%20have%20to%20work%20overtime%20and%20learn%20new%20skills.%20The%20upside%20of%20this%20is%20that%20you%20get%20the%20opportunity%20to%20learn%20many%20new%20skills%20on%20the%20job%20and%20find%20out%20what%20interests%20you%20the%20most%20in%20your%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Startups%20don't%20usually%20pay%20as%20much%20as%20Big%20Tech%20companies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20a%20startup%20company's%20stock%20options%20are%20usually%20not%20very%20lucrative.%20There%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fai-stocks-artificial-intelligence-bull-market-outlook-2024-investing-strategy-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexceptions%20with%20unicorn%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20OpenAI%20and%20SpaceX%20where%20the%20value%20of%20your%20company%20stocks%20can%20rise%20exponentially.%20But%2C%20these%20are%20the%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20startups%20are%20a%20great%20experience%20if%20you%20want%20to%20be%20a%20founder%20yourself.%20As%20an%20employee%2C%20you%20will%20get%20to%20witness%20the%20ups%20and%20downs%20and%20inner%20workings%20of%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20build%20a%20company.%20I%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20how%20to%20build%20my%20own%20business%20from%20working%20at%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%20is%20a%20very%20different%20experience%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20like%20a%20challenge%20and%20want%20to%20work%20closely%20with%20your%20coworkers%2C%20startups%20are%20a%20great%20place%20to%20work.%20But%20working%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%20is%20very%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20at%20Amazon%20for%20four%20months%20and%20worked%20at%20Google%20for%20two%20years.%20Here%20are%20the%20things%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20when%20accepting%20a%20role%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Applying%20for%20a%20job%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%20is%20very%20mechanical%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20look%20for%20job%20postings%20and%20apply%20along%20with%20hundreds%20of%20other%20applicants.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-it-takes-to-hire-hired-banking-tech-report-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIf%20your%20application%20gets%20accepted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20will%20go%20through%20four%20to%20five%20rounds%20of%20interviews.%20If%20you're%20a%20junior%20engineer%2C%20this%20includes%20mostly%20coding%20interview%20tests.%20If%20you%20are%20a%20senior%20engineer%2C%20you%20will%20have%20coding%20interview%20tests%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20system%20design%20interview%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Having%20a%20reference%20who%20works%20at%20the%20Big%20Tech%20company%20you're%20applying%20to%20is%20a%20big%20plus%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20make%20your%20application%20stand%20out%20is%20by%20having%20someone%20who%20works%20in%20the%20company%20refer%20you.%20You%20could%20reach%20out%20to%20a%20former%20classmate%20from%20college%20who%20works%20at%20the%20company%20or%20you%20can%20go%20to%20online%20tech%20forums%20or%20in-person%20tech%20meetups%20and%20meet%20people%20who%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20use%20them%20as%20a%20referral.%20This%20is%20lucrative%20for%20the%20referral%20as%20well%20because%20they%20could%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnike-pilots-5000-dollar-referral-program-for-some-technology-jobs-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%245%2C000%20for%20every%20new%20employee%20they%20refer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Working%20at%20a%20unicorn%20tech%20startup%20can%20help%20you%20stand%20out%20to%20Big%20tech%20recruiters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20way%20to%20get%20noticed%20by%20Big%20Tech%20recruiters%20is%20if%20you%20work%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-unicorn-startups-created-this-year-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunicorn%20startup%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20put%20it%20on%20your%20LinkedIn.%20The%20recruiters%20will%20reach%20out%20to%20you%20to%20apply%20to%20their%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Company%20culture%20is%20very%20important%20at%20Big%20Tech%20companies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20final%20stages%20of%20the%20interview%20process%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20company%20culture.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20had%20to%20memorize%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.jobs%2Fcontent%2Fen%2Four-workplace%2Fleadership-principles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmazon%20Leadership%20Principles%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Amazon.%20At%20Google%2C%20I%20took%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-googleyness-hiring-training-guide-change-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGoogleyness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20interview%20where%20they%20assessed%20if%20I'd%20fit%20with%20the%20Google%20company%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Employees%20don't%20always%20make%20more%20money%20at%20Big%20Tech%20companies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20think%20they'll%20make%20more%20money%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company.%20This%20isn't%20always%20true.%20Yes%2C%20you%20get%20paid%20more%20and%20get%20stock%20options%20with%20higher%20value%20at%20Big%20Tech%2C%20but%20the%20stock%20options%20could%20stay%20very%20stable.%20If%20you%20join%20a%20unicorn%20startup%2C%20the%20stock%20options%20can%20increase%20exponentially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-researcher-quit-google-openai-bard-training-on-chatgpt-report-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20who%20left%20Google%20to%20work%20at%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20were%20told%20this%20was%20a%20bad%20idea%2C%20but%20now%20they've%20made%20so%20much%20money%20just%20from%20the%20OpenAI%20stock%20options.%20They%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20that%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20Amazon%20is%20typically%20easier%20to%20get%20into%20than%20Google%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20all%20the%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20I've%20found%20that%20Amazon%20is%20one%20of%20the%20easier%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20to%20get%20into%20and%20Google%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20difficult.%20This%20is%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-managers-performance-reviews-hire-to-fire-internal-turnover-goal-2021-5%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20has%20a%20company%20culture%20of%20hiring%20and%20firing%3C%2Fa%3E%20quickly.%20However%2C%20at%20Google%2C%20it's%20very%20difficult%20to%20get%20fired%20so%20they're%20more%20careful%20when%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20a%20very%20different%20culture%20from%20Google%20and%20other%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20because%20it%20is%20an%20MBA-run%20company.%20The%20people%20at%20the%20top%20are%20business%20people%2C%20not%20engineers.%20So%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fabout-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecompany%20values%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20frugality%20and%20putting%20the%20customer%20first%20tend%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20the%20business%20aspect%20of%20the%20company%20rather%20than%20the%20technological%20aspect.%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20could%20make%20engineers%20feel%20less%20supported%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Google%20and%20most%20other%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20the%20people%20at%20the%20top%20are%20engineers%20themselves%20so%20their%20company%20values%20focus%20more%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20technology%20and%20they%20support%20engineers%20more.%20This%20is%20why%2C%20unlike%20Amazon%2C%20they%20also%20provide%20more%20perks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECoding%20interviews%20are%20just%20like%20an%20SAT%20or%20GRE%20test%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20you%20want%20to%20work%20at%20a%20startup%20or%20Big%20Tech%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhackerrank-programming-skills-top-companies-test-most-often-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20coding%20interview%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20parts%20of%20getting%20the%20job.%20It's%20an%20essential%20step%20for%20entering%20the%20industry.%20The%20key%20to%20effective%20practice%20lies%20in%20a%20structured%20learning%20approach%2C%20which%20involves%20identifying%20common%20patterns%2C%20studying%20them%2C%20and%20achieving%20mastery.%20Learning%20how%20to%20pass%20the%20coding%20interview%20tests%20can%20set%20you%20up%20for%20your%20entire%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20software%20engineer%20is%20a%20rewarding%20career.%20You%20get%20paid%20well%20and%20have%20many%20options%20of%20which%20company%20to%20work%20for.%20Regardless%20of%20which%20type%20of%20company%20you%20work%20for%2C%20you%20need%20to%20work%20for%20what%20you%20truly%20believe%20in%20instead%20of%20giving%20in%20to%20the%20hype.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-vs-startup-company-size-culture-differences-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703333341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%