tRadio%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20made%20the%20eggnog%20recipe%20that%20Martha%20Stewart%20uses%20each%20year%20during%20the%20festive%20season.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20compared%20it%20to%20my%20mom's%20favorite%20holiday%20drink%2C%20a%20Puerto%20Rican%20staple%20called%20coquito.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoth%20drinks%20use%20raw%20eggs%2C%20but%20Stewart's%20eggnog%20lacked%20sweetness%20and%20was%20more%20time-consuming%20to%20make.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENothing%20says%20happy%20holidays%20like%20taking%20a%20sip%20of%20a%20delicious%20festive%20drink.%C2%A0I%20know%20that%2C%20and%20I%20suspect%20that%20food%20and%20TV%20icon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmartha-stewart-morning-routine-early-riser-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMartha%20Stewart%3C%2Fa%3E%20does%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStewart%2C%2082%2C%20says%20that%20she%20makes%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marthastewart.com%2F355404%2Fmarthas-classic-eggnog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclassic%20eggnog%20recipe%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20holidays%20each%20year.%20Meanwhile%2C%20my%20family's%20go-to%20festive%20beverage%20is%20coquito%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpuerto-rican-thanksgiving-stuffing-recipe-photos-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Puerto%20Rican%20Christmas%20staple%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20similar%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-people-drink-eggnog-christmas-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeggnog%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20that%20the%20recipe%20calls%20for%20eggs%20and%20booze%2C%20but%20its%20Christmassy%20flavors%20are%20derived%20from%20cinnamon%20and%20cloves%20rather%20than%20nutmeg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20I've%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmoms-coquito-recipe-christmas-dinner-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20mom's%20coquito%20recipe%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20try%20something%20new%20this%20year%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20attempt%20Stewart's%20eggnog%20recipe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20high%20hopes%2C%20but%20spoiler%20alert%3A%20Stewart's%20eggnog%20doesn't%20hold%20a%20candle%20to%20my%20mom's%20coquito.%20Read%20on%20to%20find%20out%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMartha%20Stewart's%20eggnog%20recipe%20is%20a%20two-day%20process%20and%20calls%20for%206-8%20ingredients%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20boozy%20you%20want%20it%20to%20be.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20ingredients%20used%20to%20make%20Martha%20Stewart's%20eggnog.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65774f3f0ec98e92f74e3103%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20ingredients%20used%20to%20make%20Martha%20Stewart's%20eggnog.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20immediately%20didn't%20love%20how%20time-consuming%20Stewart's%20recipe%20would%20be.%20Unlike%20coquito%2C%20which%20you%20drink%20right%20after%20making%2C%20Stewart's%20eggnog%20process%20involves%20preparing%20most%20of%20the%20ingredients%20a%20day%20before%20serving%20to%20allow%20the%20flavors%20to%20%26quot%3Bmeld.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ingredients%20it%20calls%20for%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E6%20large%20eggs%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%BE%20cup%20of%20superfine%20sugar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20cups%20of%20whole%20milk%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E3%20cups%20of%20heavy%20cream%2C%20plus%20more%20for%20garnish%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%BD%20cup%20of%20bourbon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%BC%20cup%20of%20dark%20rum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%BC%20cup%20of%20cognac%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFreshly%20grated%20nutmeg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20a%20huge%20fan%20of%20mixing%20different%20alcohols%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20focus%20on%20bourbon.%20To%20supplement%20the%20missing%20rum%20and%20cognac%2C%20I%20upped%20the%20content%20of%20bourbon%20to%20a%20whole%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20first%20step%20involved%20separating%20the%20egg%20yolks%20from%20the%20whites.%20I%20messed%20up%20the%20first%20time%20around%2C%20which%20became%20a%20problem%20down%20the%20line.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223726%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20tiniest%20bit%20of%20yolk%20in%20the%20whites%20can%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20whip%20them.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657767607a3c8094d5dbc319%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222622%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20tiniest%20bit%20of%20yolk%20in%20the%20whites%20can%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20whip%20them.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccidentally%20leaving%20a%20few%20drops%20of%20yolk%20in%20the%20whites%20meant%20that%20any%20attempt%20to%20whip%20them%20until%20stiff%20peaks%20formed%20was%20futile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20realized%20my%20mistake%20the%20following%20day%20when%20it%20came%20time%20to%20beat%20the%20whites.%20Roughly%20half%20an%20hour%20in%2C%20all%20I%20had%20to%20account%20for%20was%20a%20very%20sore%20arm%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20confusion.%20Turning%20to%20Google%20in%20search%20of%20advice%2C%20I%20came%20across%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bonappetit.com%2Fstory%2Fwhipping-egg-whites%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBon%20App%C3%A9tit%3C%2Fa%3E%20article%20explaining%20that%20the%20smallest%20trace%20of%20yolk%20in%20egg%20whites%20can%20be%20disastrous%20if%20you%20are%20trying%20to%20whip%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20my%20attempt%20to%20whip%20the%20original%20batch%20of%20egg%20whites%20was%20near%20impossible%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20throw%20in%20the%20towel%20and%20start%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20it%20from%20me%20and%20be%20super%20careful%20during%20this%20step%20if%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20this%20annoying%20stumbling%20block.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20next%20step%20was%20whipping%20the%20egg%20yolks%20until%20they%20were%20thick%20and%20pale%2C%20and%20adding%20in%20the%20sugar.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20the%20sugar%20slowly%20and%20beat%20the%20mixture%20bit%20by%20bit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6577729d58e7c0c29a2bd092%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdd%20the%20sugar%20slowly%20and%20beat%20the%20mixture%20bit%20by%20bit.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20step%20was%20simple%20enough%2C%20although%20no%20matter%20how%20hard%20I%20tried%2C%20my%20egg%20yolks%20didn't%20seem%20to%20get%20significantly%20paler%20as%20I%20whipped%20them.%20I%20chalked%20it%20up%20to%20buying%20a%20good%20set%20of%20fresh%20eggs%2C%20which%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20do%20since%20the%20recipe%20does%20involve%20me%20consuming%20them%20raw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20or%20drinking%20raw%20eggs%20can%20be%20considered%20dangerous.%20As%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fweird-things-about-eggs-that-arent-true-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsuming%20raw%20eggs%3C%2Fa%3E%20carries%20the%20risk%20of%20contracting%20salmonella.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStewart's%20recipe%20does%20advise%20people%20to%20use%20the%20%26quot%3Bfreshest%20eggs%26quot%3B%20they%20can%20find%20if%20they%20decide%20to%20try%20making%20her%20eggnog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAfterward%2C%20I%20added%20the%20whole%20milk%20and%20gave%20the%20mixture%20another%20whisk.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20the%20whole%20milk.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657773f758e7c0c29a2bd214%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdding%20the%20whole%20milk.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20the%20milk%20turned%20the%20yellowish%20mixture%20much%20paler%2C%20which%20made%20it%20look%20super%20similar%20to%20coquito.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20also%20added%20two%20cups%20of%20the%20heavy%20cream%2C%20reserving%20the%20last%20to%20whip%20up%20at%20the%20end.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223899%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20heavy%20cream%20had%20a%20few%20lumps.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657774f10ec98e92f74e4e9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20heavy%20cream%20had%20a%20few%20lumps%20even%20though%20it%20was%20fresh.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Stewart's%20recipe%2C%20I%20poured%20in%20two%20cups%20of%20the%20cream%20and%20saved%20the%20last%20to%20turn%20into%20whipped%20cream%20that%20would%20be%20used%20to%20thicken%20up%20the%20eggnog%20right%20before%20serving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20mentioned%2C%20the%20mixture%20at%20this%20point%20started%20to%20look%20more%20and%20more%20like%20my%20mom's%20coquito%2C%20although%20it%20was%20a%20lot%20less%20thick%20since%20coquito%20uses%20condensed%2C%20evaporated%2C%20and%20coconut%20milk%20rather%20than%20heavy%20cream%20and%20whole%20milk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFinally%2C%20it%20was%20time%20to%20add%20a%20little%20booze%20to%20the%20eggnog.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223685%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pouring%20a%20cop%20of%20Maker's%20Mark%20bourbon%20into%20the%20mixture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657776250ec98e92f74e4f8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPouring%20a%20cup%20of%20Maker's%20Mark%20bourbon%20into%20the%20mixture.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20big%20into%20bourbon%2C%20so%20I%20followed%20Stewart's%20recommendation%20and%20bought%20a%20bottle%20of%20Maker's%20Mark%20to%20spike%20my%20eggnog%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20using%20the%20%C2%BD%20cup%20the%20recipe%20originally%20called%20for%2C%20I%20went%20for%20a%20full%20cup%20to%20account%20for%20the%20missing%20portions%20of%20rum%20and%20cognac.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESo%20far%2C%20Stewart's%20recipe%20was%20simple%20enough%2C%20but%20it%20lacked%20the%20Christmassy%20smells%20that%20I%20love%20when%20making%20coquito.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222389%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Giving%20the%20eggnog%20a%20final%20mix.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6577775758e7c0c29a2bd5db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222820%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGiving%20the%20eggnog%20a%20final%20mix.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20fun%20of%20making%20coquito%20is%20that%20the%20spices%20involved%20in%20the%20process%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0cinnamon%20and%20clove%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0are%20so%20pungent%20and%20rich%20that%20they%20quite%20literally%20make%20your%20kitchen%20smell%20like%20Christmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20that%20was%20lacking%20with%20Stewart's%20recipe.%20At%20this%20stage%2C%20the%20eggnog%20smelled%20faintly%20of%20eggs%2C%20booze%2C%20and%20not%20much%20else.%20I%20also%20wondered%20how%20those%20flavors%20would%20be%20balanced%20with%20the%20small%20amount%20of%20sugar%20that%20the%20recipe%20called%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20poured%20the%20eggnog%20into%20a%20container%20with%20a%20lid%20and%20left%20it%20in%20the%20fridge%20overnight%2C%20as%20Stewart's%20recipe%20instructs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20after%20realizing%20the%20mistake%20with%20my%20original%20egg%20whites%2C%20I%20whipped%20up%20a%20new%20batch%20and%20added%20them%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20chilled%20eggnog%20mixture.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223413%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20the%20whipped%20egg%20whites%20into%20the%20mixture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65777b8e58e7c0c29a2bd9cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222842%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdding%20the%20whipped%20egg%20whites%20into%20the%20mixture.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20an%20electric%20mixer%2C%20I'd%20recommend%20using%20it%20to%20whip%20the%20egg%20whites%20because%20even%20when%20there%20isn't%20any%20yolk%20impeding%20the%20process%2C%20it%20takes%20at%20least%2015%20minutes%20of%20whisking%20to%20get%20stiff%20peaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20egg%20whites%20finally%20started%20to%20thicken%20up%2C%20I%20couldn't%20help%20but%20notice%20at%20this%20step%20how%20gray%20they%20were%2C%20which%20wasn't%20exactly%20appetizing.%20According%20to%20several%20food%20blogs%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmilkandhoneythebakery.com%2F5-things-separating-you-from-achieving-perfect-meringue%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Milk%20and%20Honey%20Bakery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20off-looking%20color%20of%20the%20egg%20whites%20was%20likely%20caused%20by%20the%20aluminum%20bowl%20I%20used%20to%20beat%20them%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20having%20gray%20whites%20like%20me%2C%20try%20using%20a%20bowl%20made%20from%20stainless%20steel%20or%20glass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20egg%20whites%20also%20didn't%20%26quot%3Bfold%26quot%3B%20into%20the%20mixture%20the%20way%20I%20expected%20them%20to.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Folding%20the%20egg%20whites%20into%20the%20mixture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65777d947a3c8094d5dbd8e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFolding%20the%20egg%20whites%20into%20the%20mixture.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gray%20lumps%20of%20egg%20white%20broke%20down%20bit%20by%20bit%20but%20didn't%20%26quot%3Bfold%26quot%3B%20seamlessly%20into%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20mixture%20like%20I%20thought%20they%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20the%20mixture%20looked%20frothier%20than%20I'd%20anticipated.%20It%20didn't%20look%20as%20if%20the%20egg%20whites%20were%20blending%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20liquid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20moved%20forward%20and%20whipped%20up%20the%20remaining%20cup%20of%20heavy%20cream%20until%20it%20resembled%20store-bought%20whipped%20cream.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223692%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20whipped%20heavy%20cream.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65777ea17a3c8094d5dbd97c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20whipped%20heavy%20cream.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20took%20far%20less%20time%20than%20whipping%20the%20egg%20whites.%20Within%20five%20minutes%20of%20whisking%2C%20the%20cup%20of%20heavy%20cream%20went%20from%20liquid%20to%20solid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20I'd%20still%20recommend%20using%20an%20electric%20mixer%20if%20you%20have%20one%20handy%20and%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20an%20unnecessary%20arm%20workout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELike%20the%20egg%20whites%2C%20the%20whipped%20cream%20didn't%20blend%20easily%20into%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20eggnog.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223602%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20the%20whipped%20cream.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65777fa77a3c8094d5dbda36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222867%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdding%20the%20whipped%20cream.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20egg%20whites%2C%20Stewart's%20instructions%20call%20for%20the%20whipped%20cream%20to%20be%20folded%20into%20the%20eggnog.%20She%20gives%20the%20option%20to%20save%20half%20of%20the%20cream%20to%20be%20added%20on%20top%2C%20which%20I%20opted%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20recipe%20makes%20it%20sound%20like%20the%20cream%20will%20merge%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20ingredients%20relatively%20easily%2C%20but%20I%20found%20that%20wasn't%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20I%20tried%20to%20get%20a%20smooth%20mixture%2C%20I%20still%20discovered%20lumps%20of%20whipped%20cream%20rising%20to%20the%20surface%2C%20which%2C%C2%A0again%2C%20did%20not%20make%20it%20look%20super%20appetizing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20was%20too%20far%20along%20to%20give%20up%2C%20though%2C%20so%20I%20pressed%20on.%20The%20final%20step%20involved%20pouring%20a%20glass%20of%20the%20eggnog%2C%20adding%20whipped%20cream%20to%20the%20top%2C%20and%20sprinkling%20it%20with%20nutmeg.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20finished%20eggnog.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657782e17a3c8094d5dbdbf3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20finished%20eggnog.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStewart's%20recipe%20calls%20for%20fresh%20nutmeg%2C%20and%20you%20can%20use%20a%20grater%20to%20sprinkle%20it%20onto%20the%20drink%20as%20a%20final%20garnish.%20I%20couldn't%20find%20fresh%20nutmeg%20in%20my%20local%20grocery%20store%2C%20so%20I%20was%20forced%20to%20use%20ground%20nutmeg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I'd%20given%20the%20beverage%20a%20good%20dusting%20of%20nutmeg%2C%20I%20was%20pretty%20pleased%20with%20its%20appearance.%20At%20a%20glance%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20the%20whipped%20cream%20on%20top%2C%20it%20looked%20pretty%20delectable.%20But%20I%20was%20keen%20to%20find%20out%20how%20it%20tasted%2C%20and%20whether%20it%20was%20any%20competition%20for%20my%20mom's%20coquito.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EUnfortunately%20for%20Stewart%2C%C2%A0this%20eggnog%20doesn't%20hold%20a%20candle%20to%20my%20mom's%20coquito%20recipe%20for%20multiple%20reasons.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coquito%20is%20richer%20in%20flavor%20and%20more%20consistent%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20texture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657784f07a3c8094d5dbddba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22958%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoquito%20is%20richer%20in%20flavor%20and%20more%20consistent%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20texture.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOh%20boy%2C%20where%20do%20I%20begin%3F%20For%20starters%2C%20this%20recipe%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20am%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20nutmeg.%20The%20smell%20of%20the%20spice%20is%20tolerable%2C%20but%20when%20I%20actually%20tasted%20it%2C%20the%20flavor%20reminded%20me%20more%20of%20soap%20than%20anything%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENutmeg%20aside%2C%20I%20found%20the%20drink%20itself%20to%20be%20lacking%20for%20several%20reasons.%20First%2C%20the%20texture%20wasn't%20consistent%2C%20in%20my%20experience%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20one%20sip%2C%20I%20got%20a%20mouthful%20of%20liquid%2C%20frothy%20egg%20whites%20(which%20had%20inexplicably%20risen%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20cup)%2C%20and%20a%20gulp%20of%20whipped%20cream.%20Flavor-wise%2C%20the%20beverage%20was%20also%20missing%20a%20lot%20of%20sweetness%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20needed%20to%20balance%20out%20all%20of%20the%20booze%20and%20eggs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20fair%2C%20the%20eggnog%20might%20have%20tasted%20differently%20if%20I'd%20added%20the%20portions%20of%20cognac%20and%20dark%20rum%20Stewart's%20recipe%20calls%20for.%20But%20I'm%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20mixing%20different%20types%20of%20alcohol%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20