C%20a%2067-year-old%20retired%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%20pilot%20who%20completed%20his%20career%20as%20an%20Airbus%20A350%20captain%20in%20November%202021.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20hired%20by%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%20in%201989%20as%20a%20flight%20engineer%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-evolution-of-transatlantic-flying-in-photos-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELockheed%20L-1011%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20plane%20Delta%20doesn't%20fly%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20and%20went%20on%20to%20captain%20five%20different%20aircraft%20across%20my%2020%20years%20in%20the%20left%20seat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20my%20aviation%20career%20has%20two%20parts.%20I%20didn't%20go%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-regional-pilots-getting-massive-pay-raise-envoy-piedmont-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregional%20route%20like%20many%20young%20aviators%20are%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%2C%20flying%20smaller%20planes%20before%20jumping%20to%20the%20majors%20by%20the%20time%20they're%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20best%20route%20for%20me%20as%20a%20young%20person%20living%20in%20lower%20Alabama%20in%20the%201970s%20was%20to%20join%20the%20military.%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20%2430-to-%2440%20million%20jets%2C%20and%20that%20was%20a%20significant%20part%20of%20my%20experience%20and%20growth%20as%20a%20pilot.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20from%20the%20military%20to%20commercial%20aviation%2C%20though%2C%20was%20an%20amazing%20leap%20forward%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20captained%20the%20Boeing%20727%20for%20Delta%2C%20I%20could%20hand-fly%20the%20aircraft%20down%20to%20100%20feet%20during%20a%20CAT%20II%20approach%2C%20which%20just%20meant%20landing%20in%20very%20low%20visibility%20conditions.%20That%20was%20lower%20than%20anything%20I%20ever%20did%20in%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20I%20was%20actually%20moving%20people%20around%20the%20world%2C%20helping%20them%20get%20to%20where%20they%20wanted%20to%20go.%20Interacting%20with%20passengers%20and%20letting%20kids%20sit%20in%20the%20cockpit%20were%20some%20of%20the%20best%20moments%20of%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Retired%20Delta%20captain%20Mark%20Stevens%20in%20the%20cockpit%20a%20of%20an%20A350.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65806317a79e5746976a73dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERetired%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%20pilot%20Mark%20Stevens%20captained%20five%20different%20aircraft%20during%20his%20time%20at%20the%20airline.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Stevens%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20some%20new%20things%2C%20like%20pushing%20an%20aircraft%20back%20from%20the%20gate%2C%20knowing%20who%20to%20call%2C%20and%20sitting%20in%20a%20cockpit%20that%20was%20much%20higher%20off%20the%20ground%20compared%20to%20the%20fighter%20jets%20I%20once%20flew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20learn%20and%20adapt%2C%20and%20I%20really%20valued%20my%20time%20as%20a%20first%20officer%20as%20it%20helped%20me%20with%20that%20transition%20from%20one%20world%20to%20another.%20Once%20I%20got%20enough%20experience%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20move%20up%20to%20captain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20another%20big%20adjustment.%20When%20you%20upgrade%20to%20captain%2C%20you%20think%20you%20have%20all%20this%20experience%2C%20but%20you%20will%20make%20mistakes%2C%20whether%20it%20be%20a%20wrong%20taxi%20instruction%20or%20a%20misunderstood%20radio%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20started%20seeing%20aviation%20as%20just%20always%20correcting%20my%20last%20mistake.%20It%20was%20something%20told%20to%20me%20by%20a%20friend%20when%20I%20first%20started%20at%20Delta%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20mentality%20I%20kept%20throughout%20my%20entire%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20the%20727%2C%20I%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-retires-md-80-series-aircraft-send-off-in-atlanta-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaptained%20the%20MD-88%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Boeing%20717%2C%20the%20Boeing%20737%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-airbus-a350-arrive-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbus%20A350%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20retiring%20in%20November%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221632%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Landing%20the%20Boeing%20717%20in%20Jamaica.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658066e750edbc52a86534fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221224%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELanding%20during%20a%20flight%20into%20Jamaica%20on%20the%20Boeing%20717%20in%202014.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Stevens%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20I%20spent%20two%20decades%20as%20a%20captain%20for%20Delta%2C%20but%20pilots%20can%20upgrade%20much%20younger%20these%20days.%20They%20could%20fly%20as%20a%20captain%20for%2035%20or%20even%2040%20years%20by%20the%20time%20they%20have%20to%20retire%20at%2065.%20That%20was%20almost%20unheard%20of%20in%20my%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20industry%20has%20changed%20significantly%20since%20I%20started.%20Before%209%2F11%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20cockpit%20doors%20weren't%20reinforced%20like%20they%20are%20today%20and%20there%20was%20no%20TSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20hired%20before%20strong%20fatigue%20regulations%2C%20so%20I%20would%20spend%2012%20hours%20in%20the%20plane%20%E2%80%94%20flying%20seven%20takeoffs%20and%20landings%20in%20one%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20technology%20on%20aircraft%20wasn't%20nearly%20as%20advanced.%20As%20a%20captain%20on%20the%20727%20trijet%2C%20we%20were%20using%20charts%20to%20get%20us%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20MD-11%2C%20we'd%20have%20to%20manually%20program%20each%20leg%20of%20a%20flight%20between%2C%20say%2C%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20Tokyo.%20We'd%20also%20have%20to%20input%20the%20winds%20and%20altitude%20at%20each%20waypoint.%20It%20was%20difficult%20and%20tedious%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20different%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20technology%20has%20improved%20so%20much%20that%20on%20the%20A350%2C%20I%20could%20simply%20download%20the%20flight%20plan%20and%20verify%20it.%20The%20human%20error%20of%20manually%20programming%20everything%20was%20taken%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20still%20warn%20pilots%20today%20that%20just%20because%20things%20are%20more%20automated%20does%20not%20relieve%20their%20responsibility%20in%20the%20cockpit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20years%20as%20a%20captain%20prepared%20me%20for%20emergency%20situations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Retired%20captain%20Mark%20Stevens%20in%20front%20of%20Delta%20A350%20engine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65806c66a79e5746976a7915%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERetired%20Delta%20captain%20Mark%20Stevens.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Stevens%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20airline%20pilot%2C%20I%20faced%20some%20emergency%20situations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20flight%20when%20I%20was%20a%20captain%20on%20the%20MD-88%2C%20my%20engine%20went%20out%20during%20takeoff%20at%205%2C000%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20fire%20coming%20from%20the%20engine%2C%20passengers%20onboard%20knew%20something%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20went%20on%20the%20intercom%20to%20explain%20what%20happened%20and%20the%20plan%20to%20land%20safely%2C%20just%20trying%20to%20keep%20everyone%20calm%20while%20simultaneously%20going%20through%20emergency%20checklists%20and%20turning%20the%20engine%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20pilots%2C%20this%20is%20something%20my%20first%20officer%20and%20I%20trained%20for%2C%20and%20we%20fortunately%20landed%20without%20any%20injuries%20or%20further%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221087%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Delta%20MD-88.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F623b4c08f083060019c66b98%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22723%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDelta%20no%20longer%20flies%20the%20MD-88%20aircraft%20(pictured)%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20fly%20the%20three-engine%20Boeing%20727%20that%20Stevens%20also%20captained.%3Cp%3ECarterAerial%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20other%20times%20I%20managed%20to%20catch%20potential%20failures%20before%20takeoff%20in%20relation%20to%20things%20like%20brakes%20and%20hydraulics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20issues%20could%20have%20turned%20into%20bigger%20ones%20had%20we%20taken%20off%2C%20and%20are%20good%20examples%20of%20what%20experience%20and%20training%20does%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20out%20making%20little%20money%2C%20but%20retired%20with%20a%20%24500%2C000%20salary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20when%20I%20was%20hired%20as%20a%20flight%20engineer%20on%20the%20L-1011%2C%20I%20made%20little%20money%20and%20had%20to%20use%20up%20all%20of%20my%20savings%20in%20the%20first%20year%20to%20get%20by.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20my%20colleagues%20were%20on%20food%20stamps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223772%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Delta%20Lockheed%20L-1011%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20in%202001.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657ca85e7a3c8094d5dda7f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222485%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Delta%20Lockheed%20L-1011%20trijet%2C%20like%20the%20one%20Mark%20Stevens%20flew%20back%20in%20the%201990s.%3Cp%3EEtienne%20De%20Malglaive%2FGamma-Rapho%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20moved%20up%2