itle%22%3A%22The%20legacy%20of%20'Captain%20Santa'%20and%20his%20'Christmas%20Tree%20Ship%2C'%20which%20sank%20into%20the%20depths%20of%20Lake%20Michigan%20more%20than%20a%20century%20ago%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Captain%20Herman%20Schuenemann%20and%20two%20crewmen%20on%20the%20deck%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BChristmas%20Tree%20Ship%26quot%3B%20called%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65831edfcefc010bea25a0ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22451%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaptain%20Herman%20Schuenemann%20and%20two%20crewmen%20on%20the%20deck%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BChristmas%20Tree%20Ship%26quot%3B%20called%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons.%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20Historical%20Society%3B%20Wisconsin%20Sea%20Grant%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20schooner%20famously%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BChristmas%20Tree%20Ship%26quot%3B%20sank%20on%20Lake%20Michigan%20more%20than%20a%20century%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20skipper%20nicknamed%C2%A0%26quot%3BCaptain%20Santa%26quot%3B%20helmed%20the%20vessel%20%E2%80%94%20and%20went%20down%20with%20its%20holiday%20shipment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20legacy%20of%20delivering%20Christmas%20trees%20to%20needy%20families%20in%20Chicago%20lives%20on%20to%20this%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Herman%20Schuenemann%20was%20beloved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20nearly%20three%20decades%20in%20the%20late%201800s%20and%20early%201900s%2C%20the%20legendary%20boat%20captain%20hauled%20loads%20of%20Christmas%20trees%20during%20the%20holiday%20season%20from%20Michigan%20to%20be%20sold%20in%20Chicago%2C%20Illinois.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20skippered%20a%20three-masted%20schooner%20famously%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BChristmas%20Tree%20Ship%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20Schuenemann%20was%20even%20better%20known%20for%20his%20generosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20year%2C%20he'd%20give%20away%20many%20of%20his%20Christmas%20trees%20for%20free%20to%20needy%20families%20in%20the%20Chicago%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchuenemann%20was%20lovingly%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BCaptain%20Santa.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20kindness%20continued%20for%20years%20until%20one%20fateful%20night%20in%201912%2C%20when%20the%20%26quot%3BChristmas%20Tree%20Ship%26quot%3B%20sank%20in%20the%20stormy%20waters%20of%20Lake%20Michigan%2C%20taking%20all%20of%20her%20crew%20down%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20story%20of%20the%20tragic%20night%2C%20and%20how%20some%20are%20keeping%20Schuenemann's%20legacy%20alive%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221210%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Rouse%20Simmons%20tied%20up%20at%20dock.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65831f7e1c5c7b8c9a0a6ad8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22964%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Rouse%20Simmons%20tied%20up%20at%20dock.%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20Historical%20Society%3B%20Wisconsin%20Sea%20Grant%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20local%20legend%20is%20born%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESchuenemann%20captained%20a%20205-ton%20ship%20called%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20exactly%20when%20he%20earned%20his%20nickname.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20stage%20of%20Herman%20Schuenemann's%20long%20career%20as%20a%20late-season%20tree%20captain%2C%20he%20was%20given%20the%20title%20of%20Captain%20Santa%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.archives.gov%2Fpublications%2Fprologue%2F2006%2Fwinter%2Fchristmas-tree.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEach%2520year%2520in%2520early%2520December%2CChristmas%2520trees%2520to%2520Chicago%2527s%2520disadvantaged.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENational%20Archives%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20historian%20Glenn%20Longacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Longacre%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20affectionate%20nickname%20was%20bestowed%20by%20Chicago's%20local%20newspapers%20and%20by%20the%20city's%20grateful%20residents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchuenemann%20and%20his%20family%20never%20got%20wealthy%20from%20selling%20Christmas%20trees%2C%20the%20archivist%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20his%20reputation%20for%20generosity%20was%20well%20established%2C%20and%20he%20delighted%20in%20presenting%20trees%20to%20many%20of%20the%20city's%20needy%20residents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20was%20proud%20of%20his%20holiday%20heroics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSchuenemann%20enjoyed%20the%20sobriquet%20and%20proudly%20kept%20newspaper%20clippings%20about%20his%20role%20as%20Captain%20Santa%20in%20his%20oilskin%20wallet%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Longacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20exact%20cause%20of%20the%20ship's%20sinking%20remains%20unknown%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMystery%20still%20surrounds%20the%20sinking%20of%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons%20on%20Lake%20Michigan%2C%20including%20the%20exact%20cause%20of%20the%20tragedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201912%2C%20the%20vessel%20was%2044%20years%20old%20and%20long%20past%20its%20prime%2C%20according%20to%20Longacre%2C%20who%20noted%20in%20his%20report%20that%20%26quot%3Btime%2C%20the%20elements%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20heavy%20loads%20of%20lumber%20had%20taken%20their%20toll%20on%20the%20vessel's%20physical%20condition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rouse%20Simmons%20set%20out%20on%20its%20final%20voyage%20with%20Schuenemann%20and%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20crew%20members%20on%20November%2022%2C%201912%2C%20from%20Thompson%2C%20Michigan%2C%20carrying%20up%20to%205%2C000%20trees%20on%20its%20deck%20and%20in%20its%20cargo%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ship%20was%20bound%20for%20Chicago%20to%20deliver%20yet%20another%20shipment%20of%20Christmas%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20eyewitnesses%20to%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons's%20departure%20claimed%20the%20ship%20looked%20like%20a%20floating%20forest%2C%26quot%3B%20Longacre%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sadly%2C%20the%20ship%20was%20caught%20in%20a%20massive%20winter%20storm%20that%20hit%20the%20lake%2C%20according%20to%20Longacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happened%20after%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons%20departed%20the%20tiny%20harbor%20at%20Thompson%20with%20its%20heavy%20load%20of%20trees%20is%20unknown%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Longacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20historian%2C%20a%20report%20from%20life-saving%20crew%20log%20books%20said%20that%20a%20schooner%20was%20spotted%20on%20the%20lake%20flying%20its%20flag%20at%20half-mast%2C%20a%20sign%20of%20distress%2C%20at%202%3A50%20p.m.%20on%20November%2023%2C%201912.%20The%20ship%20vanished%20out%20of%20sight%20before%20rescuers%20could%20arrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchuenemann%20and%20his%20crew%20were%20never%20seen%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221094%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20bow%20of%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons%20shipwreck%20with%20a%20Christmas%20tree%20placed%20on%20its%20deck.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658451241c5c7b8c9a0af359%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22821%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20bow%20of%20the%20Rouse%20Simmons%20shipwreck%20with%20a%20Christmas%20tree%20placed%20on%20its%20deck.%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20Historical%20Society%3B%20Wisconsin%20Sea%20Grant%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20Schuenemann's%20family%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20ship%20was%20lost%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagomaritimemuseum.org%2Fchristmas-tree-ships.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Chicago%20Maritime%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20soon%2C%20his%2023-year-old%20daughter%20Elsie%20would%20show%20%26quot%3Bcourage%20beyond%20her%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20museum.%20She%20began%20making%20Christmas%20wreaths%20and%20took%20up%20her%20father's%20mantle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20became%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BThe%20Queen%20of%20Christmas%20T