aid.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20student%20loans%2C%20like%20so%20many%20of%20my%20friends%20are%20in%20%24100%2C000%20in%20debt%20and%20student%20loans%20just%20to%20get%20a%20job%20that%20pays%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20feel%20very%20thankful%20and%20privileged%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20costs%20of%20college%20may%20outweigh%20the%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20just%20not%20worth%20it%20for%20some%20young%20people%20to%20pay%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20tuition%20%E2%80%94%20and%20take%20on%20thousands%20more%20in%20student%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20risk%20getting%20a%20job%20that%20might%20not%20even%20make%20use%20of%20their%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAna%20Hern%C3%A1ndez%20Kent%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20with%20the%20Institute%20for%20Economic%20Equity%20at%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%2C%20highlighted%20that%20dilemma%20in%20November%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fopen-vault%2F2023%2Fnovember%2Fto-some-gen-z-adults-college-seems-less-likely-to-pay-off%3Futm_source%3Dtwitter%26utm_medium%3DSM%26utm_content%3Dstlouisfed%26utm_campaign%3D29039a01-b4f0-45de-a502-0dce91117a25%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Gen%20Z's%20perspectives%20on%20higher%20education.%20According%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%202022%20Survey%20of%20Household%20Economics%20and%20Decisionmaking%2C%20Kent%20found%20that%20less%20than%20half%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20are%20Black%2C%20Hispanic%2C%20women%2C%20and%20went%20to%20college%20but%20didn't%20graduate%2C%20thought%20%26quot%3Bthe%20lifetime%20financial%20benefits%20of%20college%20would%20outweigh%20the%20costs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I'm%20talking%20to%20younger%20people%20of%20Gen%20Z%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20they're%20very%20aware%2C%20and%20that%20might%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20shift.%20So%20instead%20of%20just%20a%20blanket%20approach%2C%20and%20assuming%20that%20they%20need%20to%20go%20to%20college%20and%20that%20it's%20going%20to%20pay%20off%2C%20they're%20much%20more%20critical%2C%26quot%3B%20Kent%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22838%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Many%20Gen%20Zers%20don't%20think%20college%20will%20pay%20off%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658203f3a79e5746976b30a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22585%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESt.%20Louis%20Federal%20Reserve%20analysis%20on%20Gen%20Zers%20attitudes%20toward%20college.%3Cp%3EAna%20Hern%C3%A1ndez%20Kent%20of%20St.%20Louis%20Federal%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKent%20said%20that%20Gen%20Z%20is%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20a%20little%20more%20critical%26quot%3B%20in%20evaluating%20the%20risks%20of%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20truly%20need%20one%20to%20be%20successful%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20availability%20of%20jobs%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20college%20degree%20could%20also%20be%20a%20driving%20force%20behind%20Gen%20Z's%20decision%20to%20forego%20a%20higher%20education.%20Joseph%20Fuller%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20and%20co-lead%20of%20the%20school's%20%26quot%3BManaging%20the%20Future%20of%20Work%26quot%3B%20initiative%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20working%20as%20truck%20driver%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-a-trucking-business-make-million-in-revenue-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20bring%20in%20six%20figures%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20those%20types%20of%20wages%20for%20jobs%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20college%20degree%20has%20spurred%20a%20rethinking%20of%20the%20value%20of%20a%20higher%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20the%2070-year%20period%20in%20which%20policymakers%20and%20social%20commentators%20and%20community%20leaders%20all%20saying%20from%20the%20hymnal%20that%20you've%20gotta%20go%20to%20college%20to%20make%20it%20in%20America%2C%20that%20headline%2C%20that%20kind%20of%20postulate%2C%20has%20been%20overthrown%2C%26quot%3B%20Fuller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20putting%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20on%20post-secondary%20institutions%20to%20think%20about%20ways%20to%20justify%20what%20they%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20Fuller%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3Bor%20to%20retrench%20so%20that%20they%20can%20live%20with%20a%20smaller%20amount%20of%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gov.%20Jared%20Polis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6582fa47a79e5746976b779c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGov.%20Jared%20Polis%20explains%20about%20his%20supplemental%20budget%20between%20Lt.%20Governor%20Dianne%20Primavera%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Lauren%20Larson%2C%20director%20of%20Governor's%20Office%20of%20State%20Planning%20%26amp%3B%20Budgeting%2C%20right%2C%20at%20Carriage%20House%20of%20Governors%20Mansion%20in%20Denver%2C%20Colorado%20on%20Thursday%2C%20January%203%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EHyoung%20Chang%2FThe%20Denver%20Post%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EColleges%20will%20have%20to%20put%20in%20the%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20colleges%20have%20been%20seeing%20a%20drop%20in%20enrollment%20as%20fewer%20young%20people%20choose%20to%20apply%20and%20attend.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnscresearchcenter.org%2Fcurrent-term-enrollment-estimates%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20National%20Student%20Clearinghouse%2C%20an%20nonprofit%20that%20provides%20education%20data%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epostsecondary%20enrollment%20continues%20to%20be%20well%20below%20post-pandemic%20levels%20as%20of%20May%2C%20with%201.16%20million%20fewer%20undergraduates%20enrolling%20compared%20to%20Spring%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ET