20increasing%20impunity%20afforded%20to%20those%20who%20claim%20themselves%20to%20be%20the%20custodians%20of%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncrease%20in%20the%20use%20of%20anti-terror%20laws%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20fundamentally%20incorrect%20here%20is%20the%20idea%20that%20all%20people%20charged%20with%20terrorism%20are%20%E2%80%98terrorists%E2%80%99.%20The%20desire%20to%20push%20this%20story%20stems%20from%20the%20current%20government%E2%80%99s%20desperation%2C%20as%20there%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20terrorism%20cases%20brought%20against%20students%2C%20activists%2C%20and%20journalists%2C%20among%20others.%20One%20merely%20needs%20to%20look%20at%20the%20rise%20in%20anti-terror%20laws%20and%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20cases%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NCRB%E2%80%99s%202022%20crime%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fncrb-data-shows-uapa-cases-increased-by-23-in-2022-while-those-under-sedition-down-by-nearly-75%2F1871719%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%2017.9%25%20increase%20in%20UAPA%2C%20with%20a%20total%20of%201%2C005%20cases%20documented%20across%20the%20country%20in%202022.%20This%20represents%20a%20significant%20increase%20from%202021%2C%20when%20814%20instances%20were%20reported%2C%20to%20796%20cases%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20very%20low%20number%20of%20convictions%20in%20these%20cases%20shows%20how%20unfairly%20and%20viciously%20people%20are%20punished%20in%20these%20cases%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20spend%20years%20in%20prison%20because%20bail%20is%20impossible%20to%20obtain.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20the%20botched-up%20investigation%20damages%20the%20crucial%20years%20of%20persons%20accused%20under%20these%20severe%20laws.%20According%20to%20data%20released%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fmonsoon-session-parliament-4690-people-arrested-under-uapa-from-2018-2020-only-149-convicted-government%23read-more%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20of%204%2C690%20people%20arrested%20between%202018%20and%202020%2C%20only%203%25%20were%20convicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20liberty%20of%20a%20citizen%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20and%20we%20need%20both%20a%20watchful%20judiciary%20providing%20a%20check%20and%20balance%20on%20the%20unrestricted%20powers%20of%20investigating%20agencies%20and%20fearless%20lawyers%20who%20represent%20the%20accused%20in%20court.%20Without%20both%2C%20democracy%20would%20fall%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20authoritarians%20eager%20to%20stifle%20due%20process.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20courts%20and%20law%20schools%20must%20not%20disregard%20the%20warning%20signs%20on%20the%20wall.%20It%20is%20even%20more%20critical%20today%20that%20law%20schools%20cultivate%20a%20%3Cem%3Etigerish%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebreed%20of%20young%20lawyers%20who%20are%20gutsy%20enough%20to%20fight%20the%20good%20fight%20on%20behalf%20of%20people%20wrongfully%20charged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKawalpreet%20Kaur%20is%20a%20practicing%20lawyer%20based%20in%20Delhi.%20She%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Law%20Network%2C%20Delhi.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703251848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22171032%2FEffect-41.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-argue-cases-for-terror-accused-why-gujarat-ministers-advice-to-law-students-is-wrong%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Implicit%20in%20such%20a%20view%20is%20that%20all%20those%20charged%20with%20terrorism%20are%20'terrorists'%2C%20which%20is%20fundamentally%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20criminal%20law.%20Rushikesh%20Patel's%20remarks%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation's%20mindset%2C%20as%20there%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20terrorism%20cases.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-argue-cases-for-terror-accused-why-gujarat-ministers-advice-to-law-students-is-wrong%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20Were%20Created%20in%20Our%20Creator's%20Image%20%E2%80%93%20Mimicry%20Is%20Our%20Manifest%20Destiny%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22183055%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%2C%20as%20is%20said%2C%20imitation%20is%20the%20sincerest%20form%20of%20flattery%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20affronted%20by%20Trinamool%20Congress%20MP%20Kalyan%20Banerjee%20mimicking%20him%2C%20Vice-President%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20should%20applaud%20the%20act%2C%20which%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20recorded%20on%20his%20cell%20phone%20and%20which%20has%20created%20a%20%3Cem%3Etoofan%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20teacup.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20mechanics%20of%20humour%20%E2%80%93%20if%20something%20as%20spontaneous%20and%20effervescent%20as%20humour%20can%20be%20associated%20with%20the%20prosaic%20nuts%20and%20bolts%20of%20mechanism%20%E2%80%93%20the%20target%20of%20humour%20must%20always%20be%20someone%20superior%20in%20power%2C%20pelf%2C%20or%20status%20than%20the%20humorist.%20Humour%20must%20be%20directed%20upwards%2C%20not%20downwards%3B%20at%20princes%2C%20not%20paupers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20it%20was%20for%20this%20subconscious%20reason%20that%20Nehru%20was%20seldom%20more%20pleased%20than%20when%20he%20was%20lampooned%20by%20cartoonists%20like%20Shankar%2C%20master%20of%20the%20graphic%20art%20of%20mimicry.%20By%20mimicking%20the%20V-P%2C%20the%20MP%20far%20from%20belittling%20him%2C%20was%20implicitly%20acknowledging%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20eminence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20term%20mimic%2C%20as%20noun%20or%20verb%2C%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20Greek%20word%20for%20imitation%2C%20%E2%80%98mimesis%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20itself%20comes%20from%20%E2%80%98mimos%E2%80%99%2C%20imitator%20or%20actor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20ancient%20Greece%2C%20mimesis%20was%20the%20foundation%20stone%20of%20all%20art%2C%20from%20poetry%20and%20drama%20to%20sculpture.%20In%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ERepublic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Plato%20distinguishes%20between%20mimesis%20and%20diegesis%2C%20which%20is%20narration.%20Think%20of%20the%20two%2C%20one%20as%20a%20novel%2C%20a%20fictive%20imagination%20of%20events%2C%20and%20the%20other%20as%20a%20diary%2C%20a%20recording%20of%20real%20happenings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMimesis%20was%20central%20to%20Aristotle%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EPoetics%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20which%20imitation%20of%20nature%20and%20the%20natural%20world%20was%20the%20basis%20of%20all%20literary%20creativity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAristotle%20deemed%20literature%2C%20to%20which%20both%20tragedy%20and%20comedy%20belong%2C%20to%20be%20more%20educative%20than%20history%2C%20as%20history%20deals%20with%20specific%20facts%20while%20literature%20is%20at%20liberty%20to%20roam%20the%20imaginary%20and%20imaginative%20realm%20of%20what%20might%20have%20been%2C%20as%20an%20imitation%20or%20mimicry%20of%20restrictive%20reality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECommentators%20and%20interpreters%20of%20the%20mimetic%20include%20Samuel%20Taylor%20Coleridge%2C%20Sigmund%20Freud%2C%20Jacques%20Derrida%2C%20Iris%20Murdoch%2C%20and%20mythologist%20Roberto%20Calasso.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20%3Cem%3ETradition%20and%20the%20Individual%20Talent%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20T.S.%20Eliot%20said%20that%20all%20creative%20writers%2C%20consciously%20or%20otherwise%2C%20reflect%20and%20echo%2C%20or%20mimic%20if%20you%20like%2C%20those%20who%20have%20preceded%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Milton%20would%20not%20have%20been%20a%20Milton%20without%20a%20preceding%20Shakespeare%2C%20nor%20for%20that%20matter%2C%20a%20T.S.%20Eliot%20a%20T.S.%20Eliot%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEliot%20was%20delighted%20when%20a%20sharp-eyed%20reader%20charged%20him%20with%20copycatting%20the%20repeated%20refrain%20of%20%E2%80%9Cfalls%20the%20shadow%E2%80%9D%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hollow%20Men%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20from%20Ernest%20Dowson%E2%80%99s%20poem%2C%20%3Cem%3ECynara%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20about%20a%20lost%20love%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20fell%20thy%20shadow%2C%20Cynara!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFar%20from%20taking%20the%20reader%E2%80%99s%20comment%20as%20an%20accusation%20of%20plagiarism%2C%20or%20imitation%2C%20Eliot%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20vindication%20of%20his%20proposition%20of%20the%20passing%20on%20of%20the%20baton%20of%20literary%20tradition%20through%20successive%20inheritors%20of%20a%20common%20legacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELess%20academically%2C%20but%20more%20amusingly%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20comic%20Tom%20Lehrer%20did%20his%20own%20take%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20imitation%20and%20mimicry%20when%20he%20sang%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CPlagiarise%2C%20plagiarise%2C%20plagiarise!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20do%20you%20think%20God%20gave%20you%20eyes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20to%20plagiarise%2C%20plagiarise%2C%20plagiarise!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMimicry%2C%20in%20myriad%20forms%2C%20is%20our%20manifest%20destiny.%20How%20could%20it%20not%20be%2C%20seeing%20that%20our%20Creator%2C%20in%20an%20act%20of%20self-mimicry%2C%20created%20us%20in%20His%20%E2%80%93%20or%20Her%20%E2%80%93%20own%20image%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJug%20Suraiya%20is%20a%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703250223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22183055%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fmimicry-jagdeep-dhankhar-kalyan-banerjee%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Keep%20this%20grand%20act%20of%20self%20mimicry%20in%20mind%2C%20Vice-President%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20should%20applaud%20MP%20Kalyan%20Banerjee's%20act%20of%20mimicking%20him.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fmimicry-jagdeep-dhankhar-kalyan-banerjee%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99d%20Cut%20My%20Saree%20Into%20Pieces%20to%20Cover%20My%20Child%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20Women%20Survive%20in%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20Detention%20Centres%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F10074737%2FIMG_3446.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcjp.org.in%2Fpregnant-in-a-detention-camp%2F%5C%22%3ERashminara%20Begum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20three-month%20pregnant%20woman%20who%20was%20placed%20in%20a%20detention%20camp%20in%20Assam%20for%20failing%20to%20prove%20her%20citizenship%2C%20has%20garnered%20significant%20national%20and%20international%20attention.%20This%20situation%20has%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20unfolding%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20the%20state%2C%20with%20several%20other%20pregnant%20women%2C%20like%20Begum%2C%20being%20sent%20to%20detention%20camps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20maximum%20number%20of%20detainees%20are%20women%2C%20the%20differential%20gendered%20experiences%20have%20not%20been%20well%20captured%2C%20thus%20calling%20for%20scholarly%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%E2%80%99%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20team%20conducted%20primary%20field%20interviews%20to%20explore%20the%20ways%20how%20the%20social%20roles%20and%20subjectivities%20of%20women%20contribute%20to%20varied%20experiences%20during%20detention.%20This%20article%20emphasises%20how%20the%20state%20utilises%20the%20bodies%20of%20female%20detainees%20as%20sites%20of%20torture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%20in%20the%20limbo%20of%20citizenship%20and%20refugee%20crisis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22161331%2Fimage-1663.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22941%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22161331%2Fimage-1663.png%20821w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22161331%2Fimage-1663-300x202.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690381%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22634%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWomen%20engaging%20in%20sports%20for%20peacebuilding%20at%20Basugaon%20village%2C%20Chirang%20district%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20are%20often%20caught%20in%20the%20web%20of%20statelessness%2C%20more%20so%20than%20men%2C%20because%20authorities%20often%20reject%20the%20documents%20they%20need%20to%20prove%20Indian%20citizenship.%20This%20issue%20essentially%20arises%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20poor%20women%20have%20fewer%20documents%20to%20establish%20their%20long-term%20ancestral%20residence%20in%20Assam.%20Consequently%2C%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20non-citizens%20are%20women%2C%20and%20they%20are%20subsequently%20detained%20in%20detention%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20women%20in%20the%20detention%20centres%20are%20middle-aged%20and%20mothers.%20Given%20that%20motherhood%20is%20given%20prime%20importance%20in%20most%20societies%2C%20many%20women%20take%20their%20children%20to%20detention%20centres%20with%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20care%20of%20them%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20gender-insensitive%20environment%20at%20detention%20centres%20do%20not%20take%20into%20account%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20mothers%20and%20their%20children%20who%20might%20accompany%20them%2C%20thus%20making%20the%20experience%20of%20female%20detainees%20more%20difficult%20to%20navigate.%20The%20case%20of%20Fatima%20Begum*%20can%20best%20substantiate%20this%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFatima%20Begum%2C%20from%20Cachar%20district%2C%20experienced%2010%20years%20of%20detention%20in%20three%20different%20centres%20with%20her%20daughter.%20She%20was%20sent%20a%20notice%20from%20the%20Foreigners%E2%80%99%20Tribunal%20when%20she%20was%20two%20months%20pregnant.%20About%20eight%20months%20later%2C%20she%20was%20declared%20a%20foreigner%20as%20a%20result%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20produce%20the%20necessary%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22163049%2Fimage-1664.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22975%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22163049%2Fimage-1664.png%20822w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22163049%2Fimage-1664-300x209.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690387%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20woman%20grabs%20the%20Frisbee%20disc%20during%20the%20parents%E2%80%99%20session%20at%20Basugaon%20village%2C%20Chirang%20district%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20she%20had%20given%20birth%20to%20a%20daughter%2C%20who%20was%20less%20than%20two%20months%20old.%20Reflecting%20back%20on%20the%20day%20she%20was%20taken%20to%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20police%20officers%20came%20to%20take%20me%2C%20I%20told%20them%20clearly%20that%20I%20would%20not%20go%20without%20my%20daughter.%20She%20was%20only%2045%20days%20old%20at%20that%20time%2C%20how%20could%20I%20go%20without%20her%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20recalling%20her%20time%20at%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20along%20with%20her%20infant%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20cut%20my%20saree%20into%20pieces%20to%20cover%20my%20child.%E2%80%9D%20She%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20I%20would%20feel%20uncomfortable%20while%20breastfeeding%20in%20the%20presence%20of%2010%20other%20people.%20But%20slowly%20I%20got%20accustomed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBodies%20of%20the%20female%20detainees%20chosen%20as%20sites%20of%20abuse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20partition%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20into%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20is%20merely%20an%20example%20reflecting%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20gender%20question%20manifests%20itself%20during%20sensitive%20border%20relations%2C%20conflicts%20or%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20of%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%2C%20where%20women%20have%20reportedly%20been%20subject%20to%20physical%20violence%20of%20several%20forms%2C%20reflects%20how%20violence%20on%20the%20bodies%20of%20women%20during%20sensitive%20border%20relations%20continues%20to%20manifest%20even%20today.%20Given%20that%20all%20detainees%20are%20inherently%20perceived%20as%20foreigners%2C%20the%20authorities%20often%20perpetrate%20violence%20on%20the%20detainees%20to%20demarcate%20the%20boundaries%20between%20%E2%80%98us%20Indians%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Bangladeshi%20other%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaheen%20Nessa*%2C%20who%20also%20lived%20in%20detention%20for%2010%20years%2C%20was%20three%20months%20pregnant%20when%20she%20was%20detained.%20She%20claimed%20that%20she%20could%20feel%20the%20movements%20of%20her%20baby%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20and%20hence%20realised%20that%20the%20baby%20was%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20she%20turned%20six%20months%20pregnant%2C%20one%20day%2C%20the%20authorities%20forcefully%20pushed%20a%20tetanus%20injection%2C%20which%20she%20claims%20was%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20death%20of%20her%20child.%20She%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20I%20told%20them%20I%20do%20not%20want%20the%20injection%20to%20be%20pushed%2C%20they%20did%20not%20listen%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20gave%20birth%20to%20a%20dead%20boy.%20They%20have%20killed%20my%20child.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENessa%20also%20recalled%20how%20her%20co-inmates%20were%20subject%20to%20physical%20violence.%20She%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20witnessed%20other%20people%20being%20tortured%20as%20well.%20One%20day%2C%20a%20woman%20did%20not%20know%20that%20rice%20was%20being%20served.%20She%20went%20late%20and%20was%20denied%20food.%20When%20she%20asked%20for%20food%2C%20she%20was%20beaten%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bodies%20of%20women%20become%20receptacles%20of%20violence%20at%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20detention%20centres.%20In%20a%20space%20that%20is%20unequipped%20to%20facilitate%20even%20the%20basic%20requirements%20of%20humans%2C%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20needs%20and%20requirements%20of%20women%2C%20mothers%20and%20children%20only%20remains%20a%20distant%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Names%20of%20interviewees%20have%20been%20changed%20to%20maintain%20confidentiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20part%20of%20an%20explainer%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%E2%80%99%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20team.%20Read%20the%20first%20part%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdetainees-sharing-cells-with-criminals-human-rights-violations-in-assams-detention-centres%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThese%20explainers%20explore%20the%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%20as%20spaces%20violating%20human%20rights%20and%20disproportionately%20affecting%20migrants.%20These%20are%20penned%20down%20from%20the%20documented%20findings%20of%20a%20recent%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20edition.%20Click%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazaadawaazcnes.wordpress.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20access%20the%20work%20of%20Azaad%20Awaaz%2C%20an%20initiative%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20working%20on%20issues%20of%20social%20exclusion%2C%20marginalisation%2C%20and%20discrimination%20experienced%20by%20vulnerable%2C%20precarious%20communities%20across%20India.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAll%20photographs%20have%20been%20taken%20by%20CNES%20researchers%20during%20field%20work%20in%20Assam.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20Samragnee%20Chakraborty%20and%20Hima%20Trisha%20M.%20are%20Senior%20Research%20Analysts%20(CNES).%20Yashovardhan%20Chaturvedi%2C%20Nitya%20Arora%2C%20Rieshav%20Chakraborty%20and%20Aman%20Chain%20are%20Research%20Assistants%20with%20CNES.%20The%20authors%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Dr.%20Salah%20Punathil%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad%20for%20his%20guidance%20and%20support.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703250011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F10074737%2FIMG_3446.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fid-cut-my-saree-into-pieces-to-cover-my-child-how-women-survive-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Most%20women%20in%20the%20detention%20centres%20are%20middle-aged%20and%20mothers.%20However%2C%20the%20gender-insensitive